      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Codebase: should be tracked with version control, eg: git\n    - only one codebase per app, but there will be many deploys of the apps.\n    - if there is multiple codebases, it's not an app - it's a distributed system\n\n2. Dependenices: explicitly declare and isolate dependencies.\n    - uses dependency isolation tool during execution to ensure that \n      no implicit dependencies “leak in” from the surrounding system.\n\n3. Config: store config in the environment\n    - strict separation of config from code.\n    - store configs in environment variables.\n\n4. Backing servivces: Treat backing services as attached resources.\n    - main idea here is that attached resources should be swapable with \n      only configuration changes.\n    - Attached resources here can be database, message broker, smtp etc.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Codebase: should be tracked with version control, eg: git\n    - only one codebase per app, but there will be many deploys of the apps.\n    - if there is multiple codebases, it's not an app - it's a distributed system\n\n2. Dependenices: explicitly declare and isolate dependencies.\n    - uses dependency isolation tool during execution to ensure that \n      no implicit dependencies “leak in” from the surrounding system.\n\n3. Config: store config in the environment\n    - strict separation of config from code.\n    - store configs in environment variables.\n\n4. Backing servivces: Treat backing services as attached resources.\n    - main idea here is that attached resources should be swapable with \n      only configuration changes.\n    - Attached resources here can be database, message broker, smtp etc.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
