      "text": "5. Build, release, run: Strictly separate build and run stages.\n    - build    -> code repo + dependenices = build artifact.\n    - release -> build artifact + deployment config = release artifact.\n    - run      -> release artifact + runtime = app deployed\n    - each of above stages should be seperate.\n\n6. Processes: Execute the app as one or more stateless processes.\n    - any process running should be stateless and share-nothing,\n      all thing should be stored in database or stateful backing service.\n    - Note: \"sticky session\" caching user session data in memory of app's\n      process. Sticky session are VIOLATION of 12 factor, don't use it,\n      instead use session state data that offers time-expiration, eg: Redis.\n\n7. Port binding: Export services via port binding\n    - instead of using apache httpd or any other external web server,\n      your app should itself listen on port.\n \n8. Concurrency: Scale out via the process model.\n    - app should be designed to scale via using multiple process.\n    - Like: http server will be used to route traffic and background \n      process will do heavy lifting.\n    - share-nothing, horizontally partitionable nature of 12-factor app processes",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "5. Build, release, run: Strictly separate build and run stages.\n    - build    -> code repo + dependenices = build artifact.\n    - release -> build artifact + deployment config = release artifact.\n    - run      -> release artifact + runtime = app deployed\n    - each of above stages should be seperate.\n\n6. Processes: Execute the app as one or more stateless processes.\n    - any process running should be stateless and share-nothing,\n      all thing should be stored in database or stateful backing service.\n    - Note: \"sticky session\" caching user session data in memory of app's\n      process. Sticky session are VIOLATION of 12 factor, don't use it,\n      instead use session state data that offers time-expiration, eg: Redis.\n\n7. Port binding: Export services via port binding\n    - instead of using apache httpd or any other external web server,\n      your app should itself listen on port.\n \n8. Concurrency: Scale out via the process model.\n    - app should be designed to scale via using multiple process.\n    - Like: http server will be used to route traffic and background \n      process will do heavy lifting.\n    - share-nothing, horizontally partitionable nature of 12-factor app processes",
