      "text": "9. Disposability: Maximize robustness with fast startup and graceful shutdown\n    - process are disposable, meaning they can be started or stopped at any time.\n    - minimize startup time\n    - shut down gracefully when they receive a SIGTERM.\n    - robust against sudden death - using queueing backend.\n\n10. Dev/prod parity: Keep development, staging, and production as similar as possible \n    - use same backing services b/w dev and prod environment. \n    - if postgres is used in prod, in dev also postgres should be used.\n    - another push to containerize your application with backing services.\n\n11. Logs: Treat logs as event streams\n    - treats logs as stream of aggregated, time-ordered events.\n    - app itself doesn’t manage log routing or storage, it simply writes its event stream\n    - storage, searching, archiving of logs is a concern of the env/infra\n    - Use log routers/collectors. Like Fluentd, cloud logging service etc.\n    - In k8s sidecar container captures and send it to storage.\n\n12. Admin processes: Run admin/management tasks as one-off processes.\n    - there are some one-off admin tasks, which need to do admin tasks like\n      database migration etc.\n    - these one-off admin process should be inside app, instead of running ad-hoc\n      script outside of app.",
